cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with radio frequency identification (RFID) systems and their estimation mechanisms. It could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it proposes a generic framework for stable and accurate tag population estimation schemes based on Kalman filter. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) as it employs techniques in extended Kalman filter (EKF) and cumulative sum control chart (CUSUM) to estimate tag population. It could also be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as RFID systems are often used in security applications. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses mathematical analysis to characterize the performance of the proposed framework in terms of estimation accuracy and convergence speed.
